DENGUE - THAILAND (02)
**********************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Dengue - Thailand 980102000000

Date: Fri, 02 Jan 1998 08:02:48 +0000
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background information on dengue in Thailand was extracted
from the GIDEON software program:
In 1988, dengue accounted for 29% of all febrile episodes in Bangkok.
Disease rates peak during July to August. Dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF)
was first reported during an explosive outbreak in 1958 (2,250 to 3,000
cases with ca. 300 deaths). 88.5% of DHF cases during 1958 to 1970 were
reported from Bangkok and Thonburi.
Reported cases of DHF are as follows:
Year Number (fatal)
1959 160 (21)
1960 1,851 (65)
1961 561 (36)
1962 5,947 (308)
1963 2,215 (173)
1964 7,763 (385)
1965 4,094 (193)
1966 5,816 (137)
1967 2,060 (65)
