[It would be useful to have attack rates, rather than numbers of cases but
if that's all we have, that's all we have. The official Thai pronouncement
that herd immunity may be decreasing sounds to me like a red herring and
that accepting increased virulence and infectivity might be an easier way
to avoid responsibility for the ever-expanding shadow of this disease. This
is true not only in Thailand, but elsewhere. - Mod.CHC
